%matplotlib inline
xs = num.linspace(0,100,100)
ys = [0 for i in range(100)]

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(xs, ys)

ball,=ax.plot([0], [0], 'ro')

def animate(i):
    ball.set_data([i], [0])
    return ball,

anim = ani.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, frames=len(xs), interval=50, blit=True)

from IPython.display import HTML 
HTML(anim.to_jshtml())

In [34]:
def deg_to_rad(deg):
    distance = 2*ma.pi
    return (deg / 360) * distance

def rad_to_deg(rad):
    distance = 2*ma.pi
    return (rad * 360) / distance

print(rad_to_deg(0.7853981633974483))
